<h2 id="more">Things to do in and around Parkdale</h2>
<p>The Parkdale Community Association operates a community hall, with wheelchair access, a commercial kitchen, sound system and outdoor bbq; they also run sports and youth justice programs. The City of Calgary maintains an outdoor skating rink and tennis courts. Parkdale is a short distance from Kensington Business Revitalization Zone, one of Calgary&rsquo;s most popular destinations for shopping and dining. Apart from the assortment of owner-run shops and famous restaurants, people will find themselves drawn to the area&rsquo;s friendly nature and artistic atmosphere, the area being overlooked by the Alberta College of Art and Design (ACAD). Across the river is the Bow River Pathway, which travels along the length of the Bow River and is a popular destination for jogging, hiking and biking/rollerblading. The pathway is an excellent place to see the natural side of Calgary and breath in the fresh mountain air brought in by the water flow.</p>
<p>Two schools are located in Parkdale, a public elementary and a private academy.</p>
<h2>Parkdale Misc.</h2>
<p>Parkdale has easy access to medical, dental and chiropractic clinics located in the Kensington BRZ and facilities at Foothills Hospital and the Alberta Children&rsquo;s Hospital. Parkdale is also home to the Landmark Collaborative Health Centre, Carewest, and the Advanced Spinal Care Centre. Adjacent to Alberta Children&rsquo;s Hospital is the Ronald McDonald House Southern Alberta. In 2011, had a population of 2,317.</p>
